>> serves: 5
>> total time: 10 minutes
>> source: Applied Kitchen

In a #mixing bowl{}, add the @unsalted butter{2%oz} and the @brie{6%oz}. Using a #hand mixer{}, beat on medium speed for about ~{1%minute}, or until the mixture is fully combined and smooth.

Add the @heavy cream{2%Tbsp} and continue to whip until light and fluffy.

Spread the whipped brie butter onto a #serving plate{}. If desired, sprinkle with @flaky sea salt{} and drizzle with @honey{}. Serve immediately with warm bread or crackers.
